    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A bit lost here can you put an example object so it's easier to understand where we are going?\n\nAs for `label` vs `value`, our rule for now is that anything that we consider \"for display\" is named `label`, `value` being a value to refine.\n\nThis is the connectRefinementList data structure:\n\n``` js\n{\nitems: [{\n  label: 'Black',\n  count: ..\n  value // state to be triggered, don't care about the internal value, just call refine(value)\n}],\nrefine,\ncurrentRefinement\n}\n```\n\nSo ultimately even for CurrentRefinement, if value was a function, we could have the exact same structure and add some metadata for the user to recompose the label if he wants to?\n\nproposal data structure for connectCurrentRefinements:\n\n``` js\n{\n  items: [{\n    label // we consider and use this for display\n    value // this is a function that you will pass to refine(value), you actually do not care about the internal representation\n    attributeName // metadata for the user\n    currentRefinement // metadata for the user\n  }],\n  refine\n}\n```\n\nWith this we have something in line with the other list connectors. What do you think?\n",
    "created_at": "2016-11-15T08:25:36Z",
